Birthdays make you a little more introspective, for it compels you to evaluate the balance sheet of your life so far lived. 
Introversion questions of your purpose on earth, your contribution & most of all are you levelling up as a decent human being. 
Some answers come to you, and some you are still seeking. 
The process of realisation is that if you can 
Live honestly
Love generously
Speak kindly 
Work ethically 
Feel compassionately 
Forgive easily
then each year your trip around the sun brings you closer to being worthy of your existence.

Dreaming of the runway or the spotlight? ✨
The Refinery isn’t just a course—it’s your transformation journey. Why Join Refinery? 

1. Learn from the best in the industry
Train under India’s top fashion choreographers, coaches, and stylists.
We don’t just teach—we transform raw talent into industry-ready professionals.

2. Become camera and runway confident
From slaying the ramp to owning your frame—confidence is built here.
We help you find your signature style and presence.

3. Understand the business of modelling
Modelling isn’t just about poses—it’s a profession.
Learn the insider know-how, contracts, castings, and brand etiquette.

4. We focus on personal grooming
Skin, hair, posture, presence—we refine it all.
Walk in as you are, walk out as your best version.

5. Networking and social grace
Make real connections with mentors and industry insiders.
Learn the art of conversation, presence, and lasting impressions.

This is where stars are shaped. Are you ready to join the next batch? DM for details 📩

✨ 3 Runway Rules That Change the Game ✨

If you’re walking the ramp, walk with intention. 
These aren’t the usual tips — they’re the subtle shifts that set you apart from just another model.

1. Lead with your collarbone, not your feet
Posture changes everything. Let your collarbone guide the walk — it instantly opens your frame and brings quiet confidence into every step.

2. Find your signature micro expression
It’s not about a big smile or a blank face. It’s that tiny smirk, subtle defiance, or a calm gaze that makes the audience feel something without saying a word.

3. Use the invisible pause at the end of the ramp
Don’t just pose and go. Pause. Let your presence settle. That one-second stillness makes your walk memorable, even after you turn away.
